Company Description
 4Cast is an AI-powered Decision Intelligence platform founded in 2018, with headquarters in Israel and a presence in the U.S. and Europe. Our platform helps organizations across industries like defense, security, energy, and healthcare make smarter, more confident decisions by analyzing data, simulating scenarios, and recommending optimal actions. We focus on enabling decision-makers to navigate complexity, manage risks, and optimize resources while adapting to your unique goals and missions. At 4Cast, we deliver clarity and certainty, allowing you to chart the best path forward.
 Role Description
 This is a full-time, on-site role for a Software Engineer based in the San Francisco Bay Area. As a Software Engineer at 4Cast, you will be involved in developing, testing, and maintaining high-performance software solutions using cutting-edge technologies. You will contribute to back-end development, design scalable systems, write clean, efficient code, and collaborate with a cross-functional team to deliver innovative solutions aligned with our platform’s mission.
 Qualifications
  A strong foundation in Computer Science concepts and principles.
Proficiency in Back-End Web Development and Software Development, including expertise in building scalable applications.
Demonstrated skills in Programming and Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) techniques and languages.
Experience with modern software development practices, including version control systems (e.g., Git) and agile methodologies.
Ability to work collaboratively in a team environment while demonstrating problem-solving skills and attention to detail.
Knowledge of AI or Decision Intelligence platforms is a plus.
Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or a related field.

