About the job
\U0001f5c2 We’re Hiring: QA Tester / Automation Engineer 
 \U0001f552 Employment Type: Full-Time
 \U0001f4bc Level: Entry-Level / Junior
We’re looking for a detail-oriented and technically driven QA Tester / Automation Engineer to join our team. In this role, you will be responsible for ensuring software quality through both manual and automated testing. You’ll work closely with developers, product managers, and business analysts to build reliable, scalable, and high-performing applications. If you’re passionate about quality assurance and eager to grow your skills in test automation, we’d love to hear from you!
\U0001f3af Key Responsibilities
Design, develop, and execute manual and automated test cases.
Build and maintain automated test scripts using modern frameworks.
Perform functional, regression, integration, and API testing.
Identify, document, and track defects, and collaborate with developers to resolve issues.
Participate in requirement reviews to ensure testability and coverage.
Maintain and improve test frameworks and testing processes.
Support CI/CD pipelines by integrating automated tests.
Prepare test reports and ensure clear documentation of testing activities.
\u2705 Requirements
Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or a related field.
Basic understanding of software testing concepts and QA methodologies.
Familiarity with at least one programming language (e.g., Java, Python, JavaScript).
Knowledge of automation tools (e.g., Selenium, Cypress, Playwright) is a plus.
Understanding of APIs and experience with API testing tools (e.g., Postman) is an advantage.
Familiarity with version control systems (e.g., Git) and CI/CD concepts is a plus.
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills.
Attention to detail and passion for delivering high-quality software.
\U0001f31f What We Offer
A collaborative and quality-focused engineering environment.
Opportunities to work on modern automation frameworks and tools.
Career growth into advanced QA, SDET, or DevOps roles.
Hands-on experience with CI/CD and real-world testing practices.
Mentorship and continuous learning opportunities.
Competitive salary and benefits package. 

