About the job
\U0001f5c2 We’re Hiring: Cloud Engineer (Entry-Level / Junior)
 \U0001f552 Employment Type: Full-Time
 \U0001f4bc Level: Entry-Level / Junior
We’re looking for a motivated and technically curious Cloud Engineer to join our team. In this role, you will support the design, deployment, and maintenance of cloud-based infrastructure and services. You’ll work closely with DevOps, development, and IT teams to ensure scalable, secure, and efficient cloud environments. If you’re passionate about cloud technologies and eager to build your career in modern infrastructure, we’d love to hear from you!
\U0001f3af Key Responsibilities
Assist in deploying, configuring, and maintaining cloud infrastructure (e.g., AWS, Azure, GCP).
Monitor cloud systems to ensure availability, performance, and security.
Support infrastructure automation using scripts and tools.
Help manage cloud resources, including compute, storage, and networking services.
Collaborate with development teams to support application deployment and scaling.
Troubleshoot cloud-related issues and provide timely resolutions.
Implement basic security best practices and access controls.
Document cloud architecture, processes, and configurations.
\u2705 Requirements
Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or a related field.
Basic understanding of cloud platforms (AWS, Microsoft Azure, or Google Cloud Platform).
Familiarity with operating systems (Linux/Windows) and networking fundamentals.
Basic knowledge of scripting (e.g., Python, Bash, or similar).
Understanding of virtualization and cloud concepts (IaaS, PaaS, SaaS).
Strong problem-solving skills and willingness to learn.
Good communication and teamwork abilities.
Internship, certification (e.g., AWS Certified Cloud Practitioner), or project experience is a plus.
\U0001f31f What We Offer
A collaborative and innovative cloud-focused environment.
Hands-on experience with modern cloud platforms and tools.
Opportunities for certification and career advancement in cloud engineering.
Exposure to real-world infrastructure and DevOps practices.
Mentorship from experienced engineers.
Competitive salary and benefits package.

