About the job
Junior Data Engineer – Role Description & Qualifications
The Junior Data Engineer will support the design, development, and maintenance of scalable data pipelines and architectures to enable efficient data collection, storage, and analysis. This role involves collaborating with data analysts, scientists, and other stakeholders to ensure data accessibility, reliability, and quality across multiple platforms. Responsibilities include building and optimizing ETL processes, integrating data from various sources, monitoring data workflows, and assisting in the development of data models. The role also includes troubleshooting data issues, documenting processes, and contributing to continuous improvement initiatives in data management and engineering practices.
Key qualifications include proficiency in programming languages such as Python, Java, or SQL, and familiarity with database technologies, both relational and NoSQL. Understanding of data warehousing, cloud platforms, and ETL frameworks is highly valued. Strong problem-solving skills, attention to detail, and the ability to work collaboratively in a team environment are essential. The ideal candidate demonstrates intellectual curiosity, analytical thinking, and effective communication skills to translate technical concepts into actionable solutions. A proactive approach to learning, interest in emerging data technologies, and commitment to building robust, efficient, and maintainable data systems are core to success in this role.

